WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:07.540 --> 00:00:12.500
Today we will be traveling about one to three
hours from Boise, Idaho north along Highway

00:00:12.500 --> 00:00:17.040
55 to the very small community of Banks.

00:00:17.040 --> 00:00:22.320
Turning east at Banks, we will then follow
Highway 17, also known as the Wildlife Canyon

00:00:22.320 --> 00:00:28.180
Scenic Byway, 9 miles to the turnoff of the
Middle Fork of the Payette River road heading

00:00:28.180 --> 00:00:30.770
to Crouch.

00:00:30.770 --> 00:00:36.460
From Crouch we travel north along Forest road
698 known as the Middle Fork Payette River

00:00:36.460 --> 00:00:43.630
Road, and discover seven campgrounds and one
cabin all located within a beautiful forest

00:00:43.630 --> 00:00:45.660
canopy.

00:00:45.660 --> 00:00:51.420
Many of the campsites are nestled next to
a creek or river providing optimal trout fishing

00:00:51.420 --> 00:00:54.980
opportunities.

00:00:54.980 --> 00:01:02.710
The Boiling Springs Cabin is available by
reservation only at www.recreation.gov and

00:01:02.710 --> 00:01:09.180
is a popular destination for those who enjoy
soaking in mineral hot springs.

00:01:09.180 --> 00:01:14.810
The cabin is accessible by car in the summer
months and by snowmobile in the winter.

00:01:14.810 --> 00:01:21.360
Constructed in 1934 by the Civilian Conservation
Corps, the two room cabin sleeps up to six

00:01:21.360 --> 00:01:25.750
people and was originally used to watch for
wildfires.

00:01:25.750 --> 00:01:29.000
The cabin has drinking water and a vault toilet.

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:33.990
Guests will need to bring some supplies and
equipment to ensure a comfortable and enjoyable

00:01:33.990 --> 00:01:35.120
stay.

00:01:35.120 --> 00:01:42.770
